parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause unexpected and sudden movements, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. It can also lead to unnecessary repair costs and vehicle downtime.
symptoms: Airbag deploys without any collision or impact
and injuries or abrasions due to airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Airbag Deployment in Crash Situations
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of airbag deployment in crash situations can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality, as the airbag is designed to provide critical safety protection in the event of a collision.
Failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can lead to loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distances, and accidents, resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: ABS brakes fail to stop the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the SRS crash sensor can lead to airbag deployment issues, and warranty disputes can cause inconvenience and financial burden to vehicle owners.
symptoms: Dealer representatives stating that the SRS crash sensor is not under warranty
leading to disputes and potential safety risks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, as the vehicle may suddenly accelerate without warning, making it difficult for the driver to maintain control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
the gas pedal remains fully depressed
the vehicle accelerates at full speed
the vehicle shuts down randomly without warning
the vehicle accelerates in reverse or park gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning throttle can cause unintended acceleration, making it difficult for the driver to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The throttle remains open after an accident
the throttle is stuck in an open position
the throttle suddenly opens to a high acceleration position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning transmission can cause unintended acceleration, making it difficult for the driver to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates forward or backward unexpectedly when shifting from drive to park
the engine accelerates unusually high when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Valve stem failure can cause tires to flatten, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stranded vehicles.
Sidewall failure can cause tire blowouts, leading to accidents, loss of control, or stranded vehicles.
Tread separation can cause loss of control, accidents, or damage to the vehicle.
The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially when the vehicle is in close proximity to other objects or vehicles.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates forward or backward unexpectedly
with the foot still on the brake

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents, injuries, and property damage.
symptoms: The ABS system fails to engage
causing the vehicle to skid or lose control
especially when braking on dry surfaces.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to collide with other objects or vehicles, resulting in accidents, injuries, and property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to stop or slow down
